hints.description: This company operates a chain of off-price retail stores selling apparel, home goods, and accessories. They source merchandise from over 20,000 vendors worldwide, offering brand-name products at significantly discounted prices. Notably, they operate under several different store banners including Marshalls, HomeGoods, and Sierra, catering to diverse customer preferences.
hints.funFact1: The company was founded in 1958 by Bernard Newman as the Zayre Corporation, initially selling five-and-dime merchandise. Newmans son, Howard Newman, later spearheaded the shift to an off-price retail model.
hints.funFact2: Ernie Holmes, a former NFL linebacker, served as the companys spokesperson for over 20 years, appearing in numerous television commercials and becoming a recognizable face for the brand.
